I"£<p>The huge diversity of logics, including <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/modal-logic-proper-enables-possible-worlds-semantics">modal logic</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/default-logic-processes-formalize-sequential-reasoning">default logic</a>, or <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tense-logic-formalizes-time">tense logic</a>, provide formal conceptual frameworks for describing, evaluating, and managing truth. Through domain-specific operators such as <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tense-logic-formalizes-time">time-related ones</a>, logics provide tools for reasoning about truth in certain complex situations.</p>
